          <msContents>
            <summary>Fragment containing the last two and a half chapters of the 'Exameron'. Written in a neat gothic hand 34 lines to a page. Last line in red. Some marginal notes in an early 16th cent. hand. Fol. 1 [prae]sidia: ut si peruigil speculator in portis sit obsidionis possit periculum/propulsare... 6v ... Ipse enim requieuit qui fecit: cui est honor, gloria, perpetuitas a se/culis et nunc et semper et omnia secula seculorum AMEN:/(red) Explicit exameron sancti ambrosii de opere sex dierum: The leaves are foliated 71-79 in a 16th cent. hand. This fragment contains Section 8, para, 49, line 22 to the end of the Sixth Day in Schenkl's edition of the 'Opera' Pars. I, pp. 240-261.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="" source="IANA">Latin</textLang>
